The issue was caused by `TrailingCommaOnDeclarationSiteRule` crashing when processing an empty enum class (e.g. `enum class Foo { }`). The rule was attempting to find the last enum entry in the class body to determine where to check for a trailing comma, but for an empty enum class, there are no entries, leading to a `NoSuchElementException`.

I fixed the issue by adding a check in `visitClass` to verify if the class body contains any `KtEnumEntry` children before proceeding. If there are no enum entries, the rule now skips the check, avoiding the crash.

I verified the fix by creating a reproduction test case `TrailingCommaOnDeclarationSiteRuleReproductionTest` with an empty enum class, which initially failed and then passed after the fix. I also ran the existing tests in `TrailingCommaOnDeclarationSiteRuleTest` to ensure no regressions.

The changes were made in `ktlint-ruleset-standard/src/main/kotlin/com/pinterest/ktlint/ruleset/standard/rules/TrailingCommaOnDeclarationSiteRule.kt`.

